         <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Plus new Trackr Radar</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/TRACKR-RADAR_WFTRACKRRDR1-_-20241101_v2.2231-970x646.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/TRACKR-RADAR_WFTRACKRRDR1-_-20241101_v2.2231-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/TRACKR-RADAR_WFTRACKRRDR1-_-20241101_v2.2231-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/TRACKR-RADAR_WFTRACKRRDR1-_-20241101_v2.2231-768x511.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/TRACKR-RADAR_WFTRACKRRDR1-_-20241101_v2.2231-1536x1022.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/TRACKR-RADAR_WFTRACKRRDR1-_-20241101_v2.2231-2048x1363.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/TRACKR-RADAR_WFTRACKRRDR1-_-20241101_v2.2231-750x499.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/TRACKR-RADAR_WFTRACKRRDR1-_-20241101_v2.2231-1140x759.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/TRACKR-RADAR_WFTRACKRRDR1-_-20241101_v2.2231-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/TRACKR-RADAR_WFTRACKRRDR1-_-20241101_v2.2231-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/TRACKR-RADAR_WFTRACKRRDR1-_-20241101_v2.2231-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>Wahoo</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Wahoo has also launched its first rearview radar unit (as well as its first light), the Trackr Radar. Originally a <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/garmin-varia-rtl515-rear-light-review\">Garmin invention</a>, rearview radars are now available from a few different brands, including <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/trek-carback-radar-tail-light\">Trek</a>, Magene and Bryton, so it’s a logical extension to Wahoo’s range.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As with other rearview radars, the Trackr Radar links up with a computer head unit via ANT+ or BLE to provide an alert when it detects an approaching vehicle. It’s compatible with other brands’ <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-bike-computers-gps-computers-for-training-navigation-and-data\">cycling computers</a>, not just Wahoo’s, as well as some <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-cycling-watch\">cycling watches</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to alerting the rider, the light flashes more rapidly to gain the approaching driver’s attention. A built-in accelerometer increases the brightness when the cyclist slows down, acting as a brake light.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wahoo claims battery life of up to 20 hours, thanks to a battery extender mode, which reduces light output when there are no vehicles sensed. There’s a rubber ladder-style mount to attach the unit to the bike’s seatpost.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Wahoo Trackr Radar is priced at £179.99  / $199.99 / € 199.99, with the availability date to be announced.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/wahoo-elemnt-bolt-roam-3\">Wahoo updates Bolt and Roam computers and adds a rearview radar to its range</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Pnorman","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"9e496aed0867d48352ed210a041d4f819810012da1af700358c84f40eeeef228","category":"Cycling"}